<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>The role of PvP groups on the EQ PvP server</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:50 a.m. 31/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> The role of PvP groups on the EQ PvP server<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1819" TARGET=_self>DarkenBane are not PKs....</A> (Holly Golightly)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>I like what DarkenBane is doing so far on the PvP server. Hopefully more players will form groups like this and adhere to similar policies of not killing members of your own race and attempting to adhere to EQs faction system. I don't expect this will be the way to go for everyone, and I know that certain powergaming individuals and groups won't be much interested in these notions. However we can lead through example and hopefully more will follow suit.
<P>FYI from what I have heard and observed of CC at least, they have not been killing members of their own race, and in other instances have attacked members of other non-evil races after being provoked (CC are halflings). I don't know if they will continue this policy indefinitely but it is commendable nontheless. The Pluggers, with whom I am associated, are also committed to following these guidelines (per Plug). I think those that are flaunting the faction system are definitely a minority, and as the numbers of organized groups continues to rise we will see that minority coming under greater pressure to reform their ways.
<P>&gt; This was a Race War, pure and simple. Nothing wrong with that.
<BR>&gt; Us Ogres have done it twice, tho without as much killing
<BR>&gt; success.
<P>&gt; DarkenBane are not PKs. I don't even consider them pure PvPers.
<BR>&gt; I think of them more as as mix of PvP and RP, mainly because
<BR>&gt; they only PvP along EQ's race factions/hatreds.
<P>&gt; Nah, Black, I think you mistook DB for KoT or that other guild I
<BR>&gt; mention far too often.
<P>&gt; Holly.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
